refactor(bank): Refactor ExpandDirectoryStructure feature

refactor(bank): Removed some of the clutter in the RVBank::Debinarize function to simplify logic and improve readability.
The earlier logic that looped through bank entries and handled multiple conditions was unwrapped into self-contained functions. This change makes the code easier to follow and reason about.
- Moreover, a new exception 'RVBankChecksumMismatch' is introduced to handle cases of digest mismatch between actual and expected, enhancing error reporting in the application

refactor(pbo): Remove static RVBank::ReadPbo Method In Favor Of More Object Constructors
- Made abstracted methods from last commit static - Refactored RVBank.cs to use new or explicit constructors instead of a static method for reading PBO files. Simplified the process of reading and initializing an RVBank object, providing better support for different sources (files, streams) and conditions.
fix: BisSynchronizable needs a rewrite. Removing event excessive event calls
fix(bank): Fix BufferToShort Logic

refactor(bank): Move To Unsigned DataTypes To Improve Accuracy In Reading Entries.
- Nothing more than UInt.MaxValue should ever be used, even if it is a ULong
fix(bank): Fix Compile Errors With DataType Changes

feat(lexer): Implement Singleton for Lexer, Parser and TokenTypes
Introduced Singleton pattern to Lexer, Parser, and TokenTypes Classes ensuring that a single instance is used throughout. All public constructors are now abstract enforcing dynamic creation of singletons when not found. Classes now inherit from new BisSingleton abstract class. This revision is mainly for maintaining a consistent state across all instances and to avoid unnecessary resource usage.

feat(lexer): Add Clear Points Of Extension; Spruce Up Framework
Made changes in the Lexer, Parser, and their respective usages to leverage abstract base classes (BisLexerAbs and BisLexerCore), improving code reusability and structure. Introduced BisLexerAbs and BisLexerCore in Parsing namespace. Rewrote existing code to diminish redundancy. This increases code scalability and readability, and prepares the groundwork for additional improvements and potential Lexer extensions.

feat(rvConfig): More Work On RvConfig Parser.
-Several changes aiming to improve the Parser and Lexer functionality within the BisUtils package. -The Lexer has seen a restructure to improve token matching and whitespace handling. Both these enhancements lead to a more robust and precise tokenization process. - The Parser has been refactored to cover various edge case scenarios and to provide more insightful error messages. Changes also include better handling of tokens and context information, leading to a more accurate parsing process. - The ILogger has been introduced to support better logging throughout these processes. The changes are a crucial part of making the BisUtils more efficient and reliable in its parsing and tokenizing tasks.
